text: The Division of Throsby was an Australian electoral division in the state of New South Wales. It was named after Charles Throsby (1777-1828), a pioneer and explorer in the areas south of Sydney. Throsby included Albion Park, Berkeley, Berrima, Blackbutt, Bowral, Cringila, Dapto, Exeter, Fitzroy Falls, Horsley, Kembla Grange, Lake Illawarra, Mittagong, Moss Vale, Oak Flats, Port Kembla, Robertson, Warrawong, Welby, Willow Vale, and parts of Warilla. ==Members== Image Member Party Term Notes Colin Hollis Labor 1984–2001 Retired Jennie George Labor 2001–2010 Retired Stephen Jones Labor 2010–2016 Transferred to the Division of Whitlam after Throsby was abolished in 2016 Jennie George was the first woman to be the President of the Australian Council of Trade Unions (ACTU) 1996-2000. ==Election results== * 2004 election results * 2007 election results * 2010 election results * 2013 election results ==References== ==Other websites== * Division of Throsby, Australian Electoral Commission * Stephen Jones website Category:Former electoral divisions of Australia Category:Electoral divisions of New South Wales Category:1984 establishments in Australia
